    She sat on the edge of a building wacthing the sun set. She longed to be home and in the arms of her love but for now she had someone to save. She had the mask pulled from her face and her usually bright blue eyes seemed lifeless. Behind her three roman guards were tied to gether and gaged striped of the armor wepons and keys. Unfortenetly they didn't know where the girl was being held. Frost pulled her mask back on and rose. Walking back to the romans she kicked them over the wall A rope held them above the ground but if it broke they would be dead. She was off she had to work quikly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=royalfogstone>Royal Fogstone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#993300>(2/19/02 9:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frost in rome</span><hr size=1> ***Fogstone had been waiting for about an hour when he spotted some movement not to far away...*** <br>
