After a very uncomfortable ride on the horse the previous day,Zel decided today she would walk. She was much more stealthy on foot anyways. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonlysippe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Lysippe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/02 5:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ravenstone.com/lig19.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> ~* Lysippe felt something licking at her face and she sat up with a start, she noticed the mouse and grunted, she picked it up by the tail and flung it as she cursed at the blasted animal, she had no idea it was Apollo.*~ <p>~*~*~* Artemis Bless the Amazons *~*~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maialino.it/musica/bsb_nick.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/02 7:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/Hollywood/Land/9121/nickc170.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Such hostility in her young veins</span><hr size=1> Apollo smacked against the wall and his flexible mouse bones enabled him to bounce about a foot away from the wall. Landing onto his back, he squirmed around and finally was able to readjust himself. Soon the &quot;mouse&quot; began to glow with a magnificent golden light only seen by Lysippe herself, infact the mouse was still only visible to her. In an instant before her stood Phoebus Apollo in all his grandeur, he levitated above the ground slightly, and inflated his golden aura, he adored the drama. He appeared in a royal blue tunic, with gold trimmings from his laurel crown to the sandels on his feet.<br>
<br>
Apollo smirked  to Lysippe and dusted himself off.<br>
&quot;Don't like mouses much eh?&quot;<br>
<br>
Walking to Hypnos the cat, Apollo grabbed it by the soft wrung of its neck and placed it outside of the cell. He bent down and whispered to it:<br>
<br>
&quot;Stay out of this...&quot; and he shooed the cat off.<br>
<br>
He walked to Lysippe who had bowed her head in respect for Apollo. Apollo smiled and lifted her head by pushing up on her chin. He ran a hand through her hair and spoke:<br>
<br>
&quot;Lysippe I, Apollo have come to you on this brisk February's eve to tell you that it is destiny for you and your sister Queen Varia of the Amazons of Chadesia to be reunited. Though this ordeal, as you probably have already seen will not be as easy as just getting you to her. I can only help so much for I do not want to tempt the Fates. Now come, I can help you out of here but I am afraid that is all I can do for now. If things get rough just remember...The Divine Twins are with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that Apollo walked through the bars of the cell. He grabbed one of the torches off the wall and began to shake it infront of the guards. To them it was as if the thing was haunted.<br>
<br>
Guard #1:What in all of Hades is going on here!<br>
Guard#2:Its that whore in the cell, see there the figures on the floor! Its magic! ::he angrily shook the cell bars:: STOP THIS NOW!!!<br>
<br>
Apollo set one of the guards tunic on fire and waited for the guards to finish themselves off.<br>
<br>
Guard#1:MY TUNIC,SOMEONE GET SOME WATER!!!<br>
Guard#2::stumbles around and neglects to realize there is a goblet of water on the desk::<br>
<br>
Apollo smirked and grabbed the both of the guards heads and smashed them together. They both fell to the floor unconscious. Walking to the desk he grabbed the goblet of water and put out the fire. Apollo then waved his hands over the bars of the cell and they opened.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, be off with you Lysippe. May Zeus be with you. Hermes speed.&quot; and he vanished. But where he vanished remained a sword in a golden sheath and a wooden whistel encrusted in diamonds and ruby's from Egypt, along with a small note that read.<br>
<br>
&quot;To Lysippe, from Phoebus Apollo of the golden bow who shoots afar...Use this sword to protect yourself when it be needed. And use the whistle if by some mishap you find yourself beyond your means...&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p>     *~*The Golden God*~*
              :o: Apollo :o: 
      God of all things Divine


