<br>
~* Lysippe looked up as Apollo formed from a mouse to the man. It didnt impress her. Nothing did anymore. She knew this was going to happen. &quot; He &quot; told her about it. But not to be disrespectful, she did appreciate it. She watched him get rid of the cat and the bars to the cell after he got rid of the guards. She kipped up to her feet and walked out slowly and cautiously. Looking around, she bent down to grab the sword. She left the whistle, she wouldnt need it. Her eyes went to the hilt of the sword..nose wrinkled, she never understood why anyone would want such an ugly thing. With all the jewels and such, it was tacky, more of an ornament then a weapon, but it was all she had for now. She looked over to the now dead soldiers and walked to them, she picked up there daggers and placed each in her boot. She then took a blanket left onthe ground and put it around her like a cape, there was enough material to pull over her head like a hood. She walked with no noise, the skill of an amazon, to the staircase that lead up. She somewhat remembered being brought down them, so up it was. She entered another large room, empty luckily...but for how long?  She went to the window. it was full dark. Easier to get around in the dark, but this place was so large she had to worry about finding the exit more then anything else. As she debated what to a do, a lone guard came behind her, sh esmelt him comming, Romans smelt very differently from Greeks...Romans had the particular smell of garbage. Without hesitation, she got the dagger from her boot and turned stabbing the soldier in the chest, she brought the dagger up from his chest into his throat. She left the dagger in his throat and searched him for a weapon, she sheathed the sword from Apollo and took the romans sword, they may have been worthless wastes of life, but they did make good weapons. &quot;He&quot; told he rin her head that the amazons were close by, it was just finding them, but, she didnt know who to look for, she hadnt seen her sister in many many years. But amazons could usually sence each other no matter what. She picked all the weapons she could find off the guard and all she could carry and was off to find the exit.*~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amazonfrost>Amazon Frost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/02 8:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The great Escape</span><hr size=1> Frost had finally found the right prison as the whole apollo ordeal was going on. She stood on the roof above the door and began to chant in acient words. As she spoke twin scimatars formed in her hands glowing blue. <br>
&quot;You will pay rome.&quot;<br>
She droped infront of the door and smiled from behind her mask to the two guards. The scimatars snaked out wide and came in slaping there blades away. A slash was giving across each stomache bring forth the wonderful blood to stain her boots. Her steps were deliberate as she made her way into the prison. Two more guards steped up and were sumarily disembowled frost clothing was quikly becoming drenched with blood. She didn't care she was on a mission and she headed deeper into the prison. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 288<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/02 9:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The great Escape</span><hr size=1> Varia rode, with Zelia walking in front of her, and the rest of her sisters at her back. The closer she got to Rome, the more her blood boiled. It was going to be a blood bath, that she knew for sure. How many Romans would die at her sword, that she was unsure of... but enough would pay. She would make certain. <br>
