<br>
Zelia's eyes darted all around,then she turned her attention to Varia,who just slayed a roman. She shook her head slightly,then turned her attention back to the view. <br>
<br>
If they were going to fight,and possibly go up against a great number of soldiers,Zelia would only hope that she wouldn't lose control and 'change',and for her own sake and everyone around her,she would definitally use all her self control. And spilling blood was not going to be an option,in her own strength,one hit can render an enemy unconsious,thats what she'd use.<br>
<br>
The closer they got to the city of rome,the more Zelia became parnoid and with good reason....<br>
<br>
As she marched at the head of the amazons,a large roman soldier,alone,came trudging toward them,with a sword in his hand. A lone soldier,that was suspicious enough on it's own. 'Why would any city only send one soldier at a time?' she pondered to herself,with a conclusion,that once these amazons acctually entered the city,thats when they would be hit with a number of soldiers. <br>
<br>
She shrugged to herself, and quickened her pace,meeting the roman soldier half way,intending to speak with him,she didn't expect it,but the roman drew his sword back in an instant and lunged the weapon forward at her. She arched her brows,and caught the blade in her bare hand. &quot;Thats not nice.&quot; She stated,then jerked the weapon away from the soldier,and tossed the weapon to the ground. The soldier then swung a large fist toward her face,but Zel didn't move,allowing him to make contact to her chin and her head jerked to the side. She blinked and looked back at him. &quot;That hurt...&quot; She returned his rude gesture,with one of her own. In one quick movement,she drew her right fist up,slamming it hard under the roman's chin,knocking all his sences a blur.<br>
<br>
The romans head jerks upword,then he fell backwords,unconsious.<br>
<br>
Zelia then looked behind her to Varia,with a look that clearly said, 'Was that okay?'  Ignoring that her hand had been cut open from the romans sword,she new that with a few more moments,her hand would be healed completely. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uiizeliaii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>II Zelia II</A> at: 2/20/02 11:05:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/02 2:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's beginning...?</span><hr size=1> Varia's eyes flashed with fire at the man who had just cut her wife, and with one swoop of her sword, she severed the Roman's head from his body. She snarled, and wiped the blood on her skirt, before she proceeded onto the next victim, breaking through the gates of the city with an agonized war cry. <p><html> <font face="Signet Roundhand ATT" size="+1"> Varia Angelina Avande </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showMessageRange?topicID=3.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showMessageRange?topicID=3.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showMessageRange?topicID=3.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=ht